main event: An unidentified object was sighted near Lubbock, Texas on October 12, 1967.

The object's flight path was observed to fall on the traffic pattern of the Lubbock Municipal Airport.
Confirmation was made that the landing lights and aircraft traffic at the Lubbock Municipal Airport were operating at the time of the sighting.
The observers were interviewed and the investigator concluded that the object sighted was likely an airplane landing at the Lubbock Municipal Airport.
The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes.
